    <example>
      <statement>
        <p>
          Graphically solve the following inequalities.
          <ol label="a." cols="2">
            <li>
              <p>
                <m>-20t^2-70t+300 \geq -5t+300</m>
              </p>
            </li>

            <li>
              <p>
                <m>-20t^2-70t+300 \lt -5t+300</m>
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </p>
      </statement>
      <solution>
        <sidebyside widths="47% 47%" margins="0%">
          <p>
            For both parts of this example, we start by graphing the equations <m>y=-20t^2-70t+300</m> and
            <m>y=-5t+300</m> and determining the points of intersection.
            You may use some piece of technology to do this,
            or perhaps you find yourself provided with these graphs, with the intersection points clearly marked
            or easy to determine.
          </p>

          <figure>
            <caption>Points of intersection for <m>y=-20t^2-70t+300</m> and <m>y=-5t+300</m></caption>
            <image width="47%">
              <description></description>

              <latex-image>
                  <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}
                      \begin{axis}[xmin=-10,xmax=6,
                      ymin=-100,ymax=400,
                      xtick={-8,-6,...,4},
                      minor xtick={-10,-9,...,6},
                      ytick={-100,0,...,300},
                      minor ytick={-50,0,...,350},
                      clip=false,
                          ]
                          \addplot+[domain=-6.55:3.05] {-20*x^2-70*x+300};
                          \addplot+[domain=-10:6] {-5*x+300};
                          \addplot[soliddot, color=fourthcolor] coordinates {(-3.25,316.25)} node[below left]{$(-3.25,316.25)$};
                          \addplot[soliddot, color=fifthcolor] coordinates {(0,300)} node[above right]{$(0,300)$};
                      \end{axis}
                  \end{tikzpicture}
                  ]]>
              </latex-image>
            </image>
          </figure>
        </sidebyside>

        <p>
          <ol label="a.">
            <li>
              <sidebyside widths="47% 47%" margins="0%">
                <stack>
                  <p>
                    To solve <m>-20t^2-70t+300 \geq -5t+300</m>,
                    we need to determine where the <m>y</m>-values of the parabola
                    are higher than (or equal to) those of the line.
                    This region is highlighted in <xref ref="figure-parabola-line-inequality">Figure</xref>.
                  </p>
                  <p>
                    We can see that this region includes all values of <m>t</m> between,
                    and including, <m>t=-3.25</m> and <m>t=0</m>.
                    So the solutions to this inequality include all values of <m>t</m> for which <m>-3.25\le t \le 0</m>.
                    We can write this solution set in <xref ref="definition-interval-notation" text="title">interval notation</xref>
                    as <m>[-3.25,0]</m>
                    or in <xref ref="definition-set-builder-notation" text="title">set-builder notation</xref>
                    as <m>\{t \mid -3.25 \leq t \leq 0\}</m>.
                  </p>
                </stack>

                <figure xml:id="figure-parabola-line-inequality">
                  <caption></caption>
                  <image width="47%">
                    <description></description>
                    <latex-image>
                        <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}
                            \begin{axis}[xmin=-10,xmax=6,
                            ymin=-100,ymax=400,
                            xtick={-8,-6,...,4},
                            minor xtick={-10,-9,...,6},
                            ytick={-100,0,...,300},
                            minor ytick={-50,0,...,350},
                            xlabel={$t$},
                            clip=false,
                                ]
                                \addplot+[domain=-6.55:3.05] {-20*x^2-70*x+300};
                                \addplot+[domain=-10:6] {-5*x+300};
                                \addplot[highlightcurve,domain=-3.25:0] {-20*x^2-70*x+300};
                                \addplot[closedinterval,color=fourthcolor] coordinates {(-3.25,0) (0,0)};
                                \addplot[soliddot, color=fourthcolor] coordinates {(-3.25,316.25)} node[below left]{$(-3.25,316.25)$};
                                \addplot[soliddot, color=fifthcolor] coordinates {(0,300)} node[above right]{$(0,300)$};
                                \addplot[guideline] coordinates {(-3.25,0) (-3.25,316.25)};
                                \addplot[guideline] coordinates {(0,0) (0,300)};
                            \end{axis}
                        \end{tikzpicture}
                        ]]>
                    </latex-image>
                  </image>
                </figure>
              </sidebyside>

            </li>

            <li>
              <sidebyside widths="47% 47%" margins="0%">
                <stack>
                  <p>
                    To now solve <m>-20t^2-70t+300 \lt -5t+300</m>,
                    we will need to determine where the <m>y</m>-values of the parabola are <em>less</em> than
                    those of the line.
                    This region is highlighted in <xref ref="figure-parabola-line-inequality-less">Figure</xref>.
                  </p>

                  <p>
                    We can see that <m>-20t^2-70t+300 \lt -5t+300</m> for all values of <m>t</m> where <m>t\lt -3.25</m> or <m>t\gt 0</m>.
                    We can write this solution set in <xref ref="definition-interval-notation" text="title">interval notation</xref> as
                    <m>(-\infty,-3.25)\cup(0,\infty)</m> or in <xref ref="definition-set-builder-notation" text="title">set-builder notation</xref> as <m>\{t\mid t\lt -3.25 \text{ or } t\gt 0\}</m>.
                  </p>
                </stack>

                <figure xml:id="figure-parabola-line-inequality-less">
                  <caption></caption>
                  <image width="47%">
                    <description></description>
                    <latex-image>
                        <![CDATA[\begin{tikzpicture}
                            \begin{axis}[xmin=-10,xmax=6,
                            ymin=-100,ymax=400,
                            xtick={-8,-6,...,4},
                            minor xtick={-10,-9,...,6},
                            ytick={-100,0,...,300},
                            minor ytick={-50,0,...,350},
                            xlabel={$t$},
                            clip=false,
                                ]
